  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Submerge the <strong>noodles</strong> in <strong>cold water</strong> in a wide pot</p>\r\n<p>Soak in the water for 5-8 min (off of the heat), or until loosened and softened</p>\r\n<p>Set the pot over a medium heat for 5-8, until warmed and tender</p>\r\n<p>Drain and rinse completely and set aside for step 7</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Zest and juice the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> straight into a processor (reserve the lime skins for step 4)</p>\r\n<p>Peel and roughly chop the <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon)</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>chilli</strong>&nbsp;roughly, discarding the stalk</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Place the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> in a pan (with a lid), cover with 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiling water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the reserved <strong>lime skins</strong> from step 2</p>\r\n<p>Add a big pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, and a lid</p>\r\n<p>Cook on a low-medium heat for 15 min or until the chicken is cooked through and tender</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>chilli</strong>, <strong>fish sauce</strong>, <strong>honey</strong>,<strong> coriander</strong>, <strong>peanuts</strong>, <strong>sesame oil</strong> <br />and <strong>soy sauce</strong> to the processor</p>\r\n<p>Blitz to a rough paste- this is your <strong>fresh chutney</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and top and tail the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Continue to peel lengths off of the carrot, until you end up with a pile of <strong>carrot 'ribbons'</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel as far as you can, then grate the inner stem</p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the cooked <strong>noodles</strong> in a large bowl with the <strong>carrot</strong>, <strong>spring onion</strong> and half the <strong>coriander chutney</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix well (use your hands here!)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the lid from the chicken pan</p>\r\n<p>Transfer the cooked <strong>chicken</strong> to a clean board, leaving the liquid behind</p>\r\n<p>Slice the chicken thinly (with a knife and fork)</p>\r\n<p>Return the chicken juice pan to a medium high heat and reduce by half </p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> chicken</strong> back to the pan, and stir in the remaining <strong>chutney</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the sliced chicken and coriander juices to the noodles and mix well</p>\r\n<p>Plate the noodles and chicken into bowls</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
  ],
